Anti-Communist Sentiment Analyzer
This tool is designed to analyze sentiments in texts with an anti-communist focus. It allows users to assess the sentiment expressed in documents related to anti-communism and generate visualizations and statistics based on the analyzed content.

Installation
To use this tool, ensure you have Python version 3.12 installed, along with the following libraries:

docx
re
PyPDF2
collections
wordcloud
matplotlib
networkx
You can install these libraries by executing the following command in your terminal:

Copy code
pip install python-docx PyPDF2 wordcloud matplotlib networkx
Usage
Once the dependencies are installed, simply run the main script sentiment_analysis.py providing the file you want to analyze as an argument. For example:

python anti_comunist_text_analysis.py


This will generate visualizations and statistics based on the sentiment expressed in the provided document.
